# 3D Model Gallery - User Guide

## Overview

The **3D Model Gallery** provides an interactive viewing experience for all generated Tripo3D models with real-time 3D preview, detailed statistics, and model management tools.

---

## Features

### 🖼️ Interactive 3D Preview
- **Real-time rendering** - See models in full 3D with lighting and materials
- **Orbit controls** - Click and drag to rotate, scroll to zoom
- **Auto-rotate** - Models spin automatically for 360° viewing
- **Grid helper** - Visual ground plane for reference
- **Bounding box** - Toggle dimension visualization
- **Wireframe mode** - View model topology

### 📊 Detailed Model Information
- **Description** - View the original generation prompt
- **Statistics** - Polygon count, vertex count, materials, textures
- **Dimensions** - Precise width, height, and depth measurements
- **Settings** - Quality level, PBR status, task ID

### 🎛️ Model Management
- **Place in Scene** - Add model to game world
- **Export Model** - Download metadata as JSON
- **Delete Model** - Remove from collection
- **Model List** - Browse all generated models

---

## How to Access

### Keyboard Shortcuts
- **B Key** - Toggle gallery from anywhere
- **ESC Key** - Close gallery
- **G then Gallery Button** - Open from generator UI

### From Generator UI
1. Press **G** to open Model Generator
2. Click **🖼️ View Gallery** button in header
3. Gallery opens with all generated models

